Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Competency hearing exhibits from 10/28/2022 inventoried on this date.
Location: BOX 793.

Defendant Tori Jamell Hutchins in court, in custody. Attorney Colleen A Taylor in court with Tori Jamell Hutchins. ADA Navjot Hira in court for State of Wisconsin. Case is set for a Competency Hearing. Doctor Matthew Seipel appeared via Zoom. Discussion regarding status of the case, and competency report. Defense contests findings in the Doctor's Report. Sworn for defense: Dr. Matthew Seipel. Testimony proceeded. State's exhibit #1, received. Court held colloquy with defendant regarding testimony. Court found the defendant has voluntarily, knowingly, and willingly waived his right NOT to testify. Defendant will testify. Sworn for defense: Tori Hutchins, defendant. Testimony proceeded. Arguments from the parties. Court addressed parties, and for reasons placed on the record found the defendant lacks substantial capacity to understand court proceedings or to assist in his own defense. Court orders proceedings suspended. Court ordered defendant committed to the Department of Health and Family Services for Institutional Care in order to restore competency within the statutory time frame with credit for 83 DAYS time served. The Court did NOT order involuntary medication administration at this time. Defendant is REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department for transportation to the designated facility. Signed Commitment order, and copy of the criminal complaint forwarded to DHS. Court orders case adjourned for Return of Doctor's Report in Branch 15.

Defendant Tori Jamell Hutchins not in court, in custody.  Attorney Colleen A Taylor appeared by video for Tori Jamell Hutchins.  Prosecuting attorney Foley J. Van Lieshout Ms. in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
CASE HEARD OFF THE RECORD DUE TO COURT REPORTER AVAILABILITY.
Court waives defendant's appearance. 
Matter before the Court for Doctor's Report Return. Parties in receipt of Dr. Seipel's report dated 9/19/2022.
Defense challenging findings.  Hearing date selected with the parties. Wisconsin Forensic Unit notified. 
Case remains calendared in Branch 15.
Competency hearing scheduled for October 28, 2022 at 03:00 pm.

Defendant Tori Jamell Hutchins appeared by video, in custody in MSDF.  Attorney Colleen Taylor appeared by video for Tori Jamell Hutchins. Prosecuting attorney Karine O'Byrne appeared by video for the State of Wisconsin. 
Court is advised by the defense there is reason to believe the defendant is not competent to proceed.  Pursuant to Sec. 971.14 (2) Wisconsin Statutes, Court found probable cause and ordered defendant examined by the Forensic Unit.  Order for Examination, signed and filed.   Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Watts, Branch 15.   Court ordered defendant REMANDED into custody of Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.
Doctor's Report Return scheduled for October 10, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Initial appearance scheduled for this date  8/26/22. Defendant is in custody at MDSF. Needs to be produced for court.  Julie S has been notified via email.
Summons mailed.  Defendant ordered into room 221 Safety Building on 8/26/22 @ 2p
